<TextSection>
  <h3 id="career-and-family">
    <span>4.</span>
    <span class="link--theme">"Career and Family"</span>
    by Claudia Goldin
  </h3>

  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <ProductCard
      title="Career and Family"
      href="https://amzn.to/3tu44A4"
      siteLink="https://amzn.to/3tu44A4"
      imgLink="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.T9hVsn0aFBcxRQpB6Q1Z_QHaLQ?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain"
    />
  </div>

  <h3 class="!mt-6 link--theme">Summary:</h3>
  <p>
    <span class="link--theme">"Career and Family"</span> by Claudia Goldin explores
    the challenges and opportunities women face in balancing careers and family life,
    offering insights into how societal structures can evolve to support gender equality
    in the workplace. Goldin's research highlights the importance of policy changes
    and workplace flexibility to promote gender equity.
  </p>

  <h3 class="link--theme">What It Teaches:</h3>
  <p>
    <span class="link--theme">"Career and Family"</span> teaches readers about the
    complexities of the gender pay gap and how changes in work arrangements and public
    policies can help women balance successful careers with family responsibilities.
    It underscores the significance of creating a supportive environment for working
    parents to achieve both professional and personal fulfillment.
  </p>

  <h3 class="link--theme">Amazon Review:</h3>
  <p class="text-sm">
    "A lot of people like to talk about the gender pay gap. This economist has
    focused on it for her research. She talks about the difference between
    flexible and greedy jobs. It is neat to see how providing for a family vs.
    caring for one cause different career decisions which pile on each other
    over time."
  </p>

